            <noteGrp type="workDesc">
               <note type="description">Commentary on the Qurʾan up to verse 253 of sura 2. Text cites K. Abkār al-afkār by Sayf al-dīn al-Āmidī (d. 631H in Damascus).</note>
               <note type="biblioComments">We have found two mss, Dügümlü Baba 9 (which has no attribution on it and no date) and Dar al-kutub 1096 tafsīr, which copies IA’s colophon and was copied in 1302H. Abrar Ahmed of the Ibn ʿArabī Foundation in Lahore has found the original copy in IA’s hand in Bayt Jamīl in Baghdad. The title is mentioned in both the lists which IA made of his own works, Fihris muʾallafāt al-shaykh al-akbar (RG142) and Ijāza li-l-malik al-Muẓaffar (RG 269), and in FM 3:64. Printed by Ghurab as Raḥma min al-Raḥmān (Damascus, 1979/1401).</note>
